job description
do you like working with big data and using it to drive decision and the direction of product that impact the life of people every day
as a data scientist dedicated to decision support and strategy at pluralsight you will have the opportunity to see a direct link between your work and business critical question insight and outcome
you will be part of an established team of top-notch collaborative data scientist working on breadth of challenge across the company and you will be working with a cutting-edge data platform for senior member of the team your responsibility will also include providing leadership and mentoring to teammate and championing data-driven decision making throughout the organization
what you will do
interact with key internal business stakeholder in our marketing product engineering sales finance corporate development strategy department to understand operational and strategic question and determine the appropriate technical approach
develop innovative analytical solution to business problem using statistical mathematical machine learning or other quantitative methodology
analyze large and complex datasets interpret trend and pattern and distill finding into actionable insight
effectively communicate result finding and insight from complex analysis to any audience particularly to company leader
collect process and cleanse data from a wide variety of source transform and convert unstructured data set into structured data for analysis
develop and implement predictive model machine learning algorithm and or optimization model
distill the assumption general approach and output of solution based on mathematical algorithm or model to business partner and company leader eliminating black box distrust
for more senior team member provide leadership and mentoring to teammate on best practice methodology and business problem solving serve a lead on project and for specific department of the business and oversee work of junior data scientist
qualifications
strong foundational knowledge of statistic and machine learning theory and technique particularly stochastic modeling time series operation research and or econometrics
excellent critical thinking problem solving and analytical skill
strong capability to manipulate and analyze complex high-volume data from a variety of source
mastery of one or more scientific programming language eg r python
fluency in big data platform spark hive impala kafka etc and relational database eg postgresql sql server
demonstrated experience delivering effective data visualization solution eg shiny apps d3 tableau
excellent communication skill and the ability to serve a an analytic translator
ability to problem solve independently and prioritize work based on anticipated business value
experience in solving operational or strategic business problem amount of work experience can vary with seniority of the applicant but hands-on experience in a business not
